  "learningObjective": "Find missing numbers in equations",
  "coreIdea": "Equations show that two expressions are equal, and we can find missing numbers.",
  "examples": [
    "3 + 5 = 8, so the missing number in 3 + ___ = 8 is 5. ➕",
    "10 - 6 = 4, so the missing number in 10 - ___ = 4 is 6. ➖",
    "5 + 2 = 7, so the missing number in ___ + 2 = 7 is 5. ➕"
  ],
  "misconceptions": [
    "Students may think the missing number is always the result of the equation.",
    "Students may confuse addition and subtraction when solving for the missing number.",
    "Students may think the blank can only be at the end of the equation."
